gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 133, Knicks 123
gameRecap.excerpt: The Celtics defeated the Knicks, 133-123. Derrick White led the way with a season-high 30 points, to go along with three rebounds and three assists for the Celtics, with Jayson Tatum (25 points, six rebounds) and Kristaps Porzingis (21 points, three rebounds) combining for 46 points in the victory. RJ Barrett tallied 23 points, three rebounds, and three assists for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Celtics improve to 16-5 in the regular season, while the Knicks fall to 12-9.
